 Port Elizabeth - Motherwell Cluster Operational Command Centre members arrested a 30-year-old male for the possession of a stolen vehicle on Thursday afternoon. According to police information, the man was arrested at around 14:00 along Cintsa Street, NU5, Motherwell, Port Elizabeth. "This followed after the OCC members spotted a suspicious blue VW Jetta parked in the yard of a house in Cintsa Street," described police spokesperson, Captain Andre Beetge. "After checking the vehicle, the members realised that it was stolen in Walmer, Port Elizabeth, earlier this month. "On following up information supplied by the home owner, the 30-year-old suspect was arrested." Capt Beetge said that the suspect  will be appearing before the Motherwell Magistrate's Court on Friday on a charge of possession of a stolen vehicle. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 